60.2	Botulism	Botulism	Botulism also known as botulinus intoxication is a rare but serious paralytic illness caused by botulinum toxin which is metabolic waste produced under anaerobic conditions by the bacterium Clostridium botulinum, and affecting a wide range of mammals, birds and fish.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Botulism1and2.JPG/230px-Botulism1and2.JPG
